Steps to Deploy React js application in ubuntu Instance using Nginx



1. sudo apt-get install nginx -y  


2. sudo apt-get install curl


3.curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_14.x | sudo -E bash -


4.sudo apt-get install -y nodejs


5.cd /var/www/html/


6.sudo rm index.nginx-debian.html


7.sudo git clone (paste the url of frontend repo)


8.cd frontend (enter into repo folder)


9.sudo npm install


10.sudo npm run build


11.sudo cp -r build /var/www/html (copy the build file to /var/www/html)


12.cd ..


13.sudo mv build/* .


14.There we can see files . so we can check with ip address only dont keep any port number end of the ip.


15.SG ports:     ssh:22 , React js :3000,  Http:80
